    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.48a"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">70-1  Neihardt Collection</note>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">48a</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">KRUPNICK &amp; ASSOCIATES, INC.</hi>
                        <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italics">Sales Betterment through research, marketing and</hi>
                        <lb/>
                    5 0 8  <hi rend="caps">N.  G R A N D  A V E.
                        <lb/>
                    S A I N T  L O U I S  3,  M O.
                        <lb/>
                    J E F F E R S O N</hi>  3-1 7 2 3       <hi rend="italics">Advertising</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>April 23, 1958</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Hello friend Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>You may have to scratch your head a little bit to remember the writer...a long, gangly man, who at 20, worshipped at your shrine...and never got over it.</p>
                
                <p>Prompting this letter is the news item about the passing of Mrs. Neihardt...of whom I hold such pleasant memories indeed.</p>
                
                <p>May I extend to you, and to the rest of the family, my symphathies<sic>sympathies</sic> at your loss. Especially because you lived such a fine and good life together...I know how sorely she is bound to be missed. On the other hand, I know too how rich must be your memories of your life together.</p>
                
                <p>And so, "Little Bull Buffalo"...It is time to be brave once again...and to remember to dwell on the rich memories of yesterday instead of the great loss of today.</p>
                
                <p>God bless you and yours.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Your friend,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Sam</signed>
                
                    <signed>Sam Kupnick</signed>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Professor John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Missouri University</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
